er hand, considering the low statistics of the fully differential\ndistribution, we introduce some integrated observables with only one kinematic\nvariable left, which are more promising to be measured due to the largely\nincreased statistics. The sensitivities of all these observables to the\ndifferent new physics scenarios are investigated in detail. Finally, assuming\nan ideal circumstance, we give an estimate of the statistical uncertainties of\nthe nine CP-conserving observables at LHCb and found that $\\tau^-\\to\n\\pi^-\\nu_\\tau$ has the highest analyzing power among the three $\\tau$ decay\nchannels.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 27 Feb 2023 13:17:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 16 May 2023 08:12:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-06-07"}
