ints\n(QCPs) in the accessible field range, a ferroelectric QCP at $B_{c1}$ =\n$7.9\\,\\text{T}$ and a magnetic QCP at $B_{c2}$ = $11\\,\\text{T}$. Field-induced\nlattice distortions, observed in the state at $T>$ $1\\,\\text{K}$ and which are\nassigned to the effect of spin-orbit interaction of the Cu$^{2+}$-ions, are\nconsidered as the key mechanism by which the magnetic field couples to the\ndielectric degrees of freedom in this material.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 27 Feb 2023 13:54:51 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 9 May 2023 12:39:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-10"}
